# Server Actions Pattern

All server actions MUST follow this structure:

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - Complete server action pattern
"use server";

import { auth } from "@/auth.config";
import { db } from "@/db";
import { revalidatePath } from "next/cache";

export async function actionName(data: ActionData) {
  // 1. Authentication check
  const session = await auth();
  if (!session?.user?.id) {
    throw new Error("No autorizado");
  }

  try {
    // 2. Database operation
    const result = await db.insert(table).values({
      ...data,
      adminId: session.user.id,
    });

    // 3. Revalidate cache
    revalidatePath("/dashboard");
    
    // 4. Return success
    return { success: true, data: result };
  } catch (error) {
    console.error("Error:", error);
    throw new Error("Error al procesar la solicitud");
  }
}
```

## Required Elements
1. **"use server"** directive at top
2. **Auth check** - Always verify session
3. **Try-catch** - Wrap database operations
4. **Spanish errors** - User-facing messages in Spanish
5. **revalidatePath** - Clear Next.js cache after mutations
6. **adminId** - Include user ID from session in records

## Common Mistakes

```typescript
// ❌ BAD - Missing auth check
export async function deleteCredit(id: string) {
  await db.delete(credits).where(eq(credits.id, id));
}

// ❌ BAD - No error handling
export async function createPayment(data: PaymentData) {
  const result = await db.insert(payments).values(data);
  return result;
}

// ❌ BAD - English error message
throw new Error("Unauthorized");

// ✅ GOOD - Spanish error message
throw new Error("No autorizado");
```
